  "description": "Spot welding (copper electrodes, 5000-20000A, 1-10 cycles at 50Hz) and seam welding (roller electrodes, overlapping spots for continuous gas-tight seams). No filler, no gas, no flux — uses resistance heating at the workpiece interface. Projection welding for nuts and brackets. Critical for automotive body assembly and battery tab welding.",
